# Phase 09 repository hardening: deterministic, byte-stable checkout.
#
# WHY THIS FILE EXISTS
# --------------------
# policy/configuration_manifest.json pins SHA-256 digests of the configuration
# components. Those digests are computed over the exact bytes on disk. On a
# Windows clone with core.autocrlf=true and no .gitattributes, checkout rewrote
# LF to CRLF, every LF-based configuration file changed hash, and
# tools/validate_application_spec.py failed with "configuration hash mismatch".
#
# See docs/phase_09.md for the full incident record and repair procedure.
#
# IMPORTANT — MIXED LINE ENDINGS IN THE ACCEPTED BASELINE
# -------------------------------------------------------
# The accepted baseline (70f3eca) is NOT uniformly LF. Fifteen tracked files
# were committed with CRLF or mixed endings, and several of them are
# hash-pinned by policy-3.3.1. For example policy/policy_rules.json contains
# 738 CRLF pairs and its pinned digest 9be9d0e4bd3192b1... is computed over
# those CRLF bytes.
#
# Normalizing those files to LF would change their SHA-256 values and therefore
# modify policy-3.3.1, which is prohibited. They are pinned below with `-text`
# so Git never converts them in either direction and their accepted bytes
# survive any clone, on any platform, under any core.autocrlf setting.
#
# Everything else is normalized to LF as ordinary tracked text.

# --- Default: detect text, always check out text as LF ----------------------
* text=auto eol=lf

# --- Text surfaces normalized to LF -----------------------------------------
*.json      text eol=lf
*.jsonl     text eol=lf
*.csv       text eol=lf
*.md        text eol=lf
*.py        text eol=lf
*.toml      text eol=lf
*.sql       text eol=lf
*.txt       text eol=lf
*.cfg       text eol=lf
*.ini       text eol=lf
*.yml       text eol=lf
*.yaml      text eol=lf
.gitignore      text eol=lf
.gitattributes  text eol=lf

# --- Windows launcher files (native CRLF) -----------------------------------
# cmd.exe requires CRLF in batch files. PowerShell tolerates LF, but CRLF is
# native on the target platform and avoids editor churn. No pre-existing blobs
# use these extensions, so declaring them here is safe.
*.bat       text eol=crlf
*.cmd       text eol=crlf
*.ps1       text eol=crlf
*.psm1      text eol=crlf
*.psd1      text eol=crlf

# --- Binary formats (never converted, never diffed as text) -----------------
*.zip       binary
*.xlsx      binary
*.xlsm      binary
*.xltx      binary
*.docx      binary
*.pdf       binary
*.png       binary
*.jpg       binary
*.jpeg      binary
*.gif       binary
*.ico       binary
*.sqlite3   binary
*.sqlite    binary
*.db        binary
*.gguf      binary
*.whl       binary
*.gz        binary
*.7z        binary
*.pyc       binary
*.woff      binary
*.woff2     binary

# --- Byte-frozen: committed with CRLF/mixed endings in the accepted baseline -
# MUST BE LAST: in .gitattributes the last matching rule wins, so these path
# rules have to follow the extension globs above in order to override them.
#
# DO NOT convert these files. Their exact bytes are load-bearing for
# policy-3.3.1 component digests and for the accepted submission manifest.
# Re-verify the list at any time with:
#   git ls-files --eol | Select-String "i/crlf|i/mixed"
policy/policy_rules.json                                         -text
policy/redaction_policy.json                                     -text
policy/baseline_intent_rules.json                                -text
policy/configuration_manifest.json                               -text
policy/config_versions/policy-3.0.0/configuration_manifest.json  -text
policy/config_versions/policy-3.2.0/configuration_manifest.json  -text
policy/config_versions/policy-3.2.0/policy_rules.json            -text
policy/config_versions/policy-3.2.0/redaction_policy.json        -text
policy/config_versions/policy-3.2.0/baseline_intent_rules.json   -text
submission/SUBMISSION_MANIFEST.json                              -text
submission/phase_reports/phase_00.md                             -text
submission/phase_reports/phase_02.md                             -text
docs/phase_reports/phase_00.md                                   -text
docs/phase_reports/phase_02.md                                   -text
src/player_triage/engine.py                                      -text
